        {
          "id": "fcd01cf2cf6f_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "d60b",
          "text": "The most critical intervention point to affect design at and across all physical scales (see graphic below) is to pay attention to the processes and patterns underlying their physical manifestations. It is critical to follow design up-stream and pay attention to how different worldviews, value systems, organising ideas and mental models shape our perception of reality. Together they inform how we ‘bring forth a world together’ (Maturana & Varela, 1992).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 241,
              "href": "https://medium.com/age-of-awareness/design-for-whole-systems-health-e700f1f030c6",
              "rel": "",
